creditline: Gift of James F. and Louise H. Bell in Memory of James S. and Sallie M. Bell
description: wine/liquor cabinet, Hepplewhite design; rectangular, all four sides ornamented with narrow moulding; broken at corners; small spiggot of brass; grooved, square, tapering legs (probably a later addition) terminate in spade feet with casters; interior, lined one-half way up with zinc is divided into six compartments for bottles
title: Cellarette
